大数据视角下的疫情防控。
Epidemic Prevention and Control in Big Data Perspective.
石光。
Shi Guang.
财经十一人                      。
Eleven finance and economics.
财经十一人。
Eleven finance and economics.
由《财经》杂志公司产业报道团队创建，研讨企业成败，探究行业兴衰，推动阳光商业。
Founded by Caijing magazine's industry report team, it explores the success or failure of enterprises, probes into the ups and downs of the industry, and promotes sunshine business.
以外来人员就业为主的地区应延迟复工，以本地人员就业为主的地区应视优先复工；适当延迟劳动密集型行业复工，优先放宽非劳动密集型行业复工；重点保障疫情防控必需、城市运行必需、群众生活必需的行业复工石光 | 文人口流动是新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情传播的主要渠道。
Areas dominated by migrant employment should delay the resumption of work, with priority given to areas where local workers are mainly employed; the resumption of work in non-labor-intensive industries should be given priority; and the flow of people is the main channel for the spread of the new coronavirus pneumonia.
本次疫情爆发恰逢春节，大规模、长距离的人口流动对疫情控制带来巨大挑战。
The outbreak coincided with the Spring Festival, a large-scale, long-range movement of people to control the epidemic poses a great challenge.
本文利用百度公司2019和2020年的人口流动大数据，分析春节前后我国的人口流向和规模，识别疫情传播渠道和防控重点。
This article uses the data of 2019 and 2020 of Baidu company to analyze the population flow and scale, identify the epidemic transmission channel and the key points of prevention and control.
其中，对2019年，我们计算了春节前后全国389个地级以上城市两两之间每日人口流动的完整数据；对2020年，计算了截至2月15日主要大城市的每日人口流动数量。
Among them, for 2019, we calculated complete data on daily population movements between the 389 cities above the Spring Festival level in the country; for 2020, the number of daily population movements in the major cities was calculated as of 15 February.
当前疫情仍处快速演变之中，且节后人口大规模流动尚未结束，可能成为新一轮疫情扩散的燃点。
The epidemic is still evolving rapidly, and large-scale movements of people after the holidays are not over, which could serve as a flashpoint for a new outbreak.
利用大数据支撑疫情分析，既要实时监测当前每日人口流动态势，也要根据往年经验预测未来趋势。
The use of big data to support epidemiological analysis requires both real-time monitoring of current daily population movements and projections of future trends based on previous years' experience.
数据表明，腊月29日（公历1月23日）武汉宣布“封城”是今年人口流动的转折点（注释[1]），在此之前，2020年和2019年相同农历日期的人口流动态势高度相似；此后，因疫情公开化，人口迁徙暂时性大幅减少。
Before Wuhan, the capital of Wuhan on January 29, the Gregorian Gregorian calendar, declared a turning point in its population flow this year (& # 91; 1 & # 93; & # 39;), after which movements between 2020 and 2019 were highly similar to those at the same lunar date; since then, population movements have temporarily declined dramatically as a result of the open epidemic.
虽然疫情爆发打破了原有流动规律，但主要是迁徙时间的分散或延迟，而迁徙方向和潜在规模可能相对稳定，大部分节前返乡人口节后最终仍会回城，成为疫情输入型扩散的重要渠道。
Although the outbreak has disrupted previous patterns of movement, it is mainly the dispersal or delay of migration times, while the direction and potential size of migration may be relatively stable, with the majority of pre-harvest returnees eventually returning to the city after the festival, becoming an important conduit for the spread of the epidemic.
本文首先分析春节前武汉人口流出的去向和规模，这是本次疫情传播的主要原因；然后在全国视角下，分析春节后重点疫区人口流动的主要渠道和时间特征，及其对疫情“二次传播”范围扩大的影响；最后提出政策建议。
This paper first analyzes the direction and scale of the population outflow from Wuhan before the Spring Festival, which is the main reason for the spread of the epidemic; then, from a national perspective, it analyzes the main channels and time characteristics of population movement in key epidemic areas after the Spring Festival and its impact on the expansion of the "secondary transmission" of the epidemic.
一、流出武汉的600万人成为疫情传播主要渠道武汉“封城”有效控制了人口外流。
The six million people who left Wuhan became the main channel of epidemic spread. Wuhan "closed city" effectively controlled the outflow of population.
进入腊月后，我国每日流动人口约1600万人。
After entering the month, China's daily floating population of about 16 million.
封城前，1月1日至23日（即腊月7日至29日）恰逢人口返乡高峰期，武汉平均每日流出25万人（注释[2]），是全国第10大人口流出城市。
Before the city was closed, from January 1 to 23 (or from July 7 to 29), during the peak of its return home, Wuhan, with an average daily outflow of 250,000 people (Ren & # 91; & # 93; & # 39; & # 39; & # 39; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 39; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45
封城后，1月24日和25日武汉流出人口分别降至14万和8万，26日后接近于零，这对减少疫情扩散起到了重要作用。
After sealing the city, the outflow from Wuhan fell to 140,000 on January 24 and 80,000 on January 25, and then to nearly zero later, which played an important role in reducing the spread of the epidemic.
但由于武汉封城已是春节前一天，绝大部分返乡人口已经流出。
But since Wuhan is the eve of the Spring Festival, the vast majority of the returning population has outflow.
按每日25万流出人口测算，1月份武汉累计流出人口约600万，成为疫情扩散的主要来源。
Measured by the outflow of 250,000 people a day, Wuhan accumulated outflow of 6 million people in January, becoming the main source of the spread of the epidemic.
从大数据看，这600万人去向有以下特征。
According to the big data, the 6 million people headed for the following characteristics.
第一，七成为湖北省内流动，三成为跨省流动。
First, seven became the internal flow of Hubei Province, and three became the inter-provincial flow.
武汉流向湖北省内其他地市的人口共计430万，占流出总数的七成。
Wuhan flows to other cities in Hubei province with a total population of 4.3 million, accounting for 70 percent of the outflow.
其中，孝感和黄冈是接收武汉回流人口最多的城市，分别约90万和80万，也是疫情重灾区。
Among them, filial piety and Huanggang are receiving Wuhan backflow population of the city, about 900,000 and 800,000, respectively, is also the most affected areas.
荆州、咸宁、鄂州、黄石、襄阳、荆门接收的武汉回流人口在20至40万，随州、仙桃、宜昌、天门在10万以上。
Jingzhou, Xianning, Huizhou, Huangshi, Xiangyang, Jingmen received 200,000 to 400,000 returning Wuhan population, Suizhou, Xiantao, Yichang, Tianmen more than 100,000.
图1 春节前武汉流出人口去向及数量：省内流动数据来源：百度公司第二，三成跨省流动中，去向以周边省市为主。
Figure 1 Before Spring Festival, Wuhan outflow of population and quantity: the province flow data source: Baidu company second, 30% interprovincial flow, mainly to the surrounding provinces and municipalities.
武汉跨省流动人口共计180万，占流出总数的三成。
Wuhan interprovincial floating population totaled 1.8 million, accounting for 30 percent of the total outflow.
其中，接收武汉回流人口最多的是河南（33万），其次是湖南（21万）；超过10万人的还有安徽（14万）、广东（13万）、江西（13万）、江苏（10万）；超过6万人的还有重庆（7万）、浙江（7万）、四川（7万）、山东（6万）、北京（6万）。
Among them, Wuhan received the largest number of returning population in Henan (330,000), followed by Hunan (210,000); Anhui (140,000), Guangdong (130,000), Jiangxi (130,000) and Jiangsu (100,000); Chongqing (70,000), Zhejiang (70,000), Sichuan (70,000), Shandong (60,000) and Beijing (60,000).
上述省市排序与当前疫情严重程度基本一致。
The ranking of provinces and municipalities is consistent with the severity of current epidemic situation.
图2 春节前武汉流出人口去向及数量：跨省流动数据来源：百度公司第三，流向大都市圈的人数多，对疫情扩散影响大。
Figure 2 Population outflow from Wuhan before Spring Festival and its amount: Cross-provincial flow data source: Baidu company is third, the number of people flowing to the metropolitan area, the spread of the epidemic has a great impact.
大城市人口密集，是人流枢纽，流向大城市的武汉人口会通过交叉传染使疫情扩散到全国各地，综合影响更大。
Large cities are densely populated, is a population hub, the flow of Wuhan population to large cities through cross-infection to spread the epidemic throughout the country, the overall impact is greater.
三大都市圈核心城市都接收了较多武汉人口，其中，北京（6.3万）是最多的，其次是上海（5.3万）、广州（3.8万）和深圳（3.6万）；其他包括南京（2.1万）、杭州（2万）、苏州（1.4万）、温州（1.3万）、天津（1万）、东莞（0.9万）、佛山（0.7万）。
The three largest metropolitan areas all have Wuhan population, with Beijing (63,000) the largest, followed by Shanghai (53,000), Guangzhou (38,000) and Shenzhen (36,000), followed by Nanjing (21,000), Hangzhou (20,000), Suzhou (14,000), Wenzhou (13,000), Tianjin (10,000), Dongguan (9,000) and Foshan (0.007 million).
总体看，主要都市圈中，流向长三角的武汉人口总计超过12万，流向珠三角的超过9万。
Overall, Wuhan people flowing to the Yangtze River Delta account for more than 120,000 of the major urban agglomerations and over 90,000 to the Pearl River Delta.
此外，流向成渝都市圈的武汉人超过10万，其中重庆（7.3万）、成都（2.8万）。
In addition, more than 100,000 Wuhan people, including 73,000 in Chongqing and 28,000 in Chengdu, are flowing into the Chengdu-Chongqing metropolitan area.
图3 春节前武汉流出人口去向及数量：主要大城市数据来源：百度公司二、高度警惕人口回流造成疫情“二次传播”武汉流向各地的人口，在春节期间与本地其他人密切接触，这种“一次传播”是疫情的主要原因。
